main event: A civilian in Chicago, Illinois reported sighting a bright, oval-shaped object with little wings that appeared to be at a standstill at 1000 pm altitude for about 30 seconds before moving swiftly out of sight.
interesting points: The object was described as bright, oval-shaped with little wings, and was observed at a standstill at 1000 pm altitude for about 30 seconds before moving out of sight.
The report was sent to U.S. Army Headquarters in Chicago and then forwarded to the Air Materiel Command at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base for further information.
The Headquarters Fifth Army in Chicago did not contemplate continuing an investigation of the matter.
The event was evaluated as unconventional aircraft by the Civilian source.
The sighting took place on April 26, 1951, at about 5:25 P.M. on the lake front at a cement road while the witness was driving south on Shore and 33rd St.
sighted object: bright, oval-shaped object with little wings
